Description: Fragment of a calcite figurine, part of the head preserved, showing some sort of beak or snout and front part of head preserved, on each side the contour of an eye in black colour drawn. The surface is smoothed from different angles, one can still see the different areas.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.20B, low level
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 111)
